<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dupuy de Lôme</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Swampscott, Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-31"><hi rend="italic">August
                                        31, 1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I offer you sincere thanks for your efficient cooperation and loyal
                            proofs of friendship. The Wilmington episode is at this moment being
                            repeated at New Orleans. I beg you will telegraph the naval and revenue
                            authorities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Dupuy de Lôme</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>